               <msContents>
                  <summary>Collection of protective prayers:&#xD; I) Lǝfāfa ṣǝdǝq “Bandlet of
                     Righteousness” (fols. 4r-20r)&#xD; II) Mangada samāy “Journey to Heaven” (fols.
                     20r-27r)&#xD; III) Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt “Teaching of Mysteries” (fols.
                     27v-38v)&#xD; IV) Ṣalota barad Prayer against hail” (fols. 38v-41v)&#xD; V)
                     Ṣalota nadarā, ʾAsmāt-prayer against a disease called nadarā which is the evil
                     eye(fols. 41v-44r) )&#xD; VI)
                     Ṣalota baʾǝnta ḥǝmāma ʿāynata sabʾ "Prayer Concerning the Desease of the Evil
                     Eye of the People" (fols. 44r-47v)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-7.</summary>
